Overall, the acer species was best explained by elevation, distance from
a stream, plotsize, and beers. Since acer is a habitat generalist, there
are more variables that could impact cover because they can surivive in
more diverse habitats. The abiefra species was best explained by
elevation, TCI, and beers. There are less factors that can predict the
cover in abifera because they are a habitat specialists. This means that
they need more specific needs than a habitat generalist like acer.
